<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Heteranthessius unisetatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., male 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
habitus, dorsal 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
urosome, ventral 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
rostrum 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
antennule 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E</emphasis>
antenna 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F</emphasis>
labrum 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G</emphasis>
mandible 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H</emphasis>
maxillule 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I</emphasis>
maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
); 0.1 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B, C</emphasis>
); 0.05 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D, E</emphasis>
); 0.02 mm(
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F-I</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rostrum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13C</figureCitation>
) broad, with round posterior margin. Antennule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13D</figureCitation>
) 335 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, seven-segmented; armature formula 3, 12+2 aesthetascs, 2, 2+aesthetasc, 4+aesthetasc, 2+aesthetasc, and 7+aesthetasc; all setae naked; aesthetascs on second, fourth, and fifth segments large, broad, longer than antennular segments; aesthetasc on sixth segment small; aesthetasc on terminal segment as long as those of proximal segments but slender. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13E</figureCitation>
) four-segmented, with armature formula 1, 1, 3, and 4+2 claws; terminal segment (third endopodal segment) gradually narrowed distally, 2.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (76 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
38 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
); two terminal claws unequal, outer longer and thicker than inner, ~ 0.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as terminal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Labrum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13F</figureCitation>
) wider than long, with shallow posteromedian incision, fringed with broad membrane along posterior margin, pair of weak, tapering lobes at posteromedial region. Mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13G</figureCitation>
) simple, with curved, elongate gnathobase bearing serrate margins. Maxillule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13H</figureCitation>
) as small, digitiform lobe tipped with one naked seta. Maxilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A habitus, dorsal B urosome, ventral C rostrum D antennule E antenna F labrum G mandible H maxillule I maxilla. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B, C); 0.05 mm (D, E); 0.02 mm (F-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720733" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">13I</figureCitation>
) as large lobe tipped with one naked seta. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A maxilliped B leg 1 C leg 2 D endopod of left leg 3 E leg 4 F endopod of right leg 4 G leg 5. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A-F); 0.02 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14A</figureCitation>
) large, consisting of three segments and terminal claw; first segment as long as wide, unarmed; large second segment with one rudiment of seta and one large tubercle ventromedially; small third segment unarmed; terminal claw large, with one spine proximally and denticles on distal half of inner margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Legs 1-4 biramous; outer seta on basis small; spines on rami with densely serrate margins. Legs 1-3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A maxilliped B leg 1 C leg 2 D endopod of left leg 3 E leg 4 F endopod of right leg 4 G leg 5. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A-F); 0.02 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14B-D</figureCitation>
) with three-segmented rami. Leg 4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Heteranthessius unisetatus sp. nov., male A maxilliped B leg 1 C leg 2 D endopod of left leg 3 E leg 4 F endopod of right leg 4 G leg 5. Scale bars: 0.05 mm (A-F); 0.02 mm (G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14E</figureCitation>
) with three-segmented exopod and one-segmented endopod. Second endopodal segment of leg 1 characteristically with two inner setae. Endopod of leg 4 small, globular, with or without inner seta. Armature formula for legs 1-4 as follows:
</paragraph>
